The paper deals with error-correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The specific types of errors considered, tandem and palindromic duplications/deletions, are related to string algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic techniques to derive bounds on the cardinality of codes, which falls under the category of algorithms and complexity (cs.DC). The topic of error-correcting codes is also relevant to coding theory (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SI).
